'''''The Last of the Jedi: Return of the Dark Side''''' is a [[Star Wars Legends|''Star Wars'' Legends]] junior novel written by [[Jude Watson]]. It is the sixth installment of the series ''[[Star Wars: The Last of the Jedi]]'', and it was first published in [[December]] [[2006]] by [[Scholastic]].

==Publisher's summary==
''Years ago, when they were both Jedi apprentices, Ferus Olin and Anakin Skywalker were rivals. Now their paths are about to cross again....''

''Abandoning the Jedi Order saved Ferus's life. As a result, he is the only one who can track down and save Jedi who have survived the rise of the Galactic Empire. He has rebellion on his mind, and hopes to bring about the fall of the Emperor''.

''Only Darth Vader stands in his way. Ferus might not realize it, but his old rival is now his new deadly enemy.''

''The thrilling new series from the ''New York Times'' bestselling author of ''Jedi Apprentice'' and ''Jedi Quest''''.

==Plot summary==
Ferus Olin remains on the planet [[Samaria/Legends|Samaria]] as a double-agent for [[Galactic Emperor/Legends|Emperor]] Palpatine. His job is to send a message to the Resistance, and ask if they will disband. Meanwhile, [[Trever Flume]], [[Astri Oddo]] and [[Lune Oddo Divinian|Lune Divinian]], [[Raina Quill]], [[Toma (resistance leader)|Toma]], [[Clive Flax]], and [[Oryon]] all remain on the secret asteroid base where [[Garen Muln]] and [[Fy-Tor-Ana|Solace]], two [[Jedi Knight/Legends|Jedi Knights]], remain alive and well helping the Resistance fighters. Toma sets up a meeting with a Resistance member named [[Eve Yarrow|Flame]], and he can't decide who to send to speak with her because of his illness. Trever steals his ship, and meets with Flame on Samaria. Meanwhile, Darth Vader is busy showing his anger to Ferus because he reminds Vader of his past. That side of him is dead. In the end, [[Aaren Larker]] is out of office because of a no-confidence call by [[Bog Divinian]]. Bog is elected as prime minister, and Larker is killed by Vader. Trever believes Ferus betrayed him and Flame by sending them to [[Rosha]], where there was an ambush.

